videos.headline: Notre Dame stuffs Stanford on third down
videos.description: On third-and-2, Cardinal RB Bryce Love takes a handoff, but is swallowed up in the backfield by a swarm of Fighting Irish defenders.

videos.headline: Notre Dame's Stepherson takes it 83 yards to the house
videos.description: Fighting Irish QB Brandon Wimbush connects with Kevin Stepherson who breaks free and goes 83 yards untouched to the end zone to give Notre Dame an early 7-0 lead.

videos.headline: Irwin makes leaping grab in end zone for Stanford TD
videos.description: Cardinal QB K.J. Costello airs it out and finds Trenton Irwin in the end zone for a 29-yard touchdown, tying the game at 7-7.

videos.headline: Costello connects with Smith to set up Stanford in red zone
videos.description: Cardinal QB K.J. Costello fakes a handoff and finds Kaden Smith open downfield for a 26-yard gain, getting Stanford down to the Notre Dame 4-yard line.

videos.headline: Cardinal's WR adjusts mid-route to reel in TD
videos.description: K.J. Costello lofts a pass to the end zone and J.J. Arcega-Whiteside comes back to the ball to catch the pass for a 4-yard touchdown, giving Stanford a 14-7 lead.

videos.headline: Kelly anticipates 'hard-fought' second half against Stanford
videos.description: Notre Dame coach Brian Kelly says both the Fighting Irish and Cardinal have played well in the first half and expects the game to "come down to the last possession."

videos.headline: Notre Dame trails Stanford at the half
videos.description: Two touchdowns from K.J. Costello have Stanford up 14-10 at halftime.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Notre Dame trails Stanford at the half) 2017/11/25 ESHEET SOTFULL

videos.headline: St. Brown tiptoes along sideline for long Fighting Irish TD
videos.description: On the first play of scrimmage in the second half, Equanimeous St. Brown takes a short pass and turns on the jets, scoring from 75 yards out to give Notre Dame a 17-14 lead.

videos.headline: Stanford's Love gets loose for big gain
videos.description: Cardinal RB Bryce Love spins around a defender and breaks free for a 31-yard pickup, setting up a Stanford field goal.

videos.headline: Stanford narrowly avoids disaster on own goal line
videos.description: Backed against its own 1-yard line, Stanford muffs the snap in the end zone, but QB K.J. Costello is able to quickly recover the ball and fall forward to avoid the safety.

videos.headline: Punt return gets Fighting Irish into red zone
videos.description: Chris Finke jukes and hurdles his way to a 41-yard punt return, getting all the way down to the Stanford 19-yard line.

videos.headline: Costello evades pressure, throws strike for Cardinal TD
videos.description: Stanford QB K.J. Costello avoids the rush in the pocket and steps forward to throw a great pass to Kaden Smith for a 19-yard touchdown, putting the Cardinal ahead 24-20.

videos.headline: Notre Dame's Wimbush picked off
videos.description: Fighting Irish QB Brandon Wimbush drops back and has his pass intercepted by Curtis Robinson who takes it back to the Notre Dame 29-yard line.

videos.headline: Stanford's Costello tosses off-balance TD pass
videos.description: K.J. Costello gets the defense to bite on play-action and throws off his back leg to connect with Dalton Schultz in the end zone for a 12-yard score.

videos.headline: Notre Dame muffs kickoff, Stanford recovers
videos.description: Fighting Irish kick returner C.J. Sanders has the ball knocked loose by Jordan Fox and Cardinal Malik Antoine recovers to complete the turnover.

videos.headline: Scarlett pounds it in as Stanford takes control
videos.description: Cardinal RB Cameron Scarlett bowls into the end zone from 3 yards out to give Stanford a commanding 38-20 lead.

videos.headline: Stanford intercepts pass in end zone
videos.description: Notre Dame turns it over for the third time in the fourth quarter as QB Brandon Wimbush throws to the end zone and has his pass picked off by Stanford's Frank Buncom.

videos.headline: Shaw: Stanford showed 'toughness and heart' in win
videos.description: Cardinal coach David Shaw lauded his team's determination in its 38-20 victory over the Fighting Irish, saying the team's grit has propelled them to win eight of the last nine games.

videos.headline: Love credits 'resiliency' for Cardinal's turnaround
videos.description: Bryce Love says Stanford never stopped working hard or believing in themselves, even after the team's 1-2 start to the season.

videos.headline: 'Electric' fourth quarter powers Stanford past Notre Dame
videos.description: Kirk Herbstreit and Chris Fowler break down Stanford's 38-20 win against Notre Dame, citing the stellar play of QB K.J. Costello as the key to the victory.
